FIBA has appointed retired Colonel Sam Ahmedu and referee, Kingsley Ojeaburu, of Nigeria, as technical officials for the  2019 FIBA World Cup African Group E qualifiers, 5th Window, in Luanda, Angola. According to the appointment letters signed by the Executive Director, FIBA Africa, Ahmedu, who is the President of FIBA Africa Zone 3 and member of the NBBF Board, will serve as a technical delegate while Ojeaburu, Nigeria’s most senior active FIBA referee, will join his colleagues to officiate  the qualifiers that will run from November 30 to December 2, 2018. Eleven-time African champions, Angola, will host the 5th window of the qualifiers featuring Angola, Tunisia, Chad, Cameroon, Egypt and Morocco. The 5th Window for Group F, featuring Nigeria, Senegal, Cote D’Ivoire, Central Africa, Mali and Rwanda, will hold in February, 2019, with Abidjan, Cote D’Ivoire as the designated host city. Nigeria, playing in Group F, were the first country to qualify for the World Cup in China, followed by Tunisia in Group E with a round of competition to spare in both groups where there are still three more qualification tickets on offer for the remaining African teams. The position of technical delegate is a new one created by FIBA for the management of all its high level competitions including the World Cup qualifiers and World Cup proper. It has the position of technical commissioner, competition manager and supervisor all rolled into one.